  <h2>When to call your pediatrician</h2>

  <p>If your baby's skin temperature is consistently elevated, if they're showing signs of distress, lethargy, difficulty breathing, or if something just doesn't feel right to you &mdash; trust your instincts and call your pediatrician. No monitor &mdash; WiFi or FHSS &mdash; replaces a parent's judgment or a doctor's care.</p>

